						<summary>

						<p>This records a gift of 45 sheep for burning a lamp every night in the gate known as Ēkanāyakaṉ-tiruvāśal built in the temple by Kurāvaṉ Rājarājaṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Vikramaśōḻa-Śōḻiyaraiyar an officer of the king. This gift is witnessed by the manager of the temple, the <hi rend="italic">Nagarattār</hi> of Tiruviḍaimarudil and the <hi rend="italic">Ūrār</hi> of Tiraimūr.</p>						

						</summary>
